            <h2>Rapunzel</h2>
            <p class="summary">

              A beautiful princess is trapped in a tower by a wicked witch. A brave prince, drawn by her enchanting voice, sets out to rescue her. But their journey is filled with twists and turns, and their love is put to the ultimate test.
            </p>
            <p class="full-content" style="display: none;">
            Once upon a time, a couple lived in a small stone hut on a hill near the woods. They wished for a child but were unsure if they'd be good parents. Behind their house was a window overlooking a beautiful garden filled with Rapunzel plants. The garden belonged to a powerful witch, and no one dared to enter it.   
           
            <br></br>
            One day, the woman gazed longingly at the Rapunzel and fell ill, craving it desperately. “I must have some, or I'll die,” she said to her husband. Out of love, the man snuck into the garden to steal the plant. The witch caught him and demanded, “How dare you steal my Rapunzel? You will pay for this!”
              <br></br>
            When their daughter was born, the witch took her away. She named her Rapunzel and raised her in a tall, doorless tower deep in the forest. Rapunzel grew into a beautiful girl with long golden hair. To visit her, the witch would call, “Rapunzel, Rapunzel, let your hair down!”

              One day, a prince heard Rapunzel singing from the tower. Enchanted by her voice, he returned daily to listen. He saw the witch climb the tower using Rapunzel's hair and decided to try himself. Calling out the same words, he climbed up and met Rapunzel.
              <br></br>
              At first, Rapunzel was startled, having never seen a man before. But the prince explained he was drawn by her voice and soon asked her to marry him. Rapunzel agreed and devised a plan: the prince would bring silk each visit so she could weave a ladder and escape with him.
              <br></br>
              “You'll never see Rapunzel again!” the witch sneered. Distraught, the prince stumbled back and fell from the tower. Though he survived, thorns blinded him.

                For years, the prince wandered the forest, living in sorrow. One day, he stumbled into the desert where Rapunzel had been banished. Hearing her familiar voice, he followed it and finally found her. Overjoyed, Rapunzel embraced him. As her tears fell onto his eyes, his sight was miraculously restored.
                
                The prince and Rapunzel returned to his kingdom with their twin children. They lived happily ever after, their love proving stronger than any spell.
                
                </p>
